# Global Docs Ownership Policy

Last updated: 2026-06-04

Scope: `/opt/Axodus/.instructions`

Status: REQ-01 recovery artifact for Global Docs / Instructions L1 to L2.

This ownership policy governs documentation and coordination records only. It does not grant production execution, wallet signing, treasury movement, trading, swaps, payouts, settlement, credential use, or on-chain writes.

## Roles

| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| Portfolio Coordinator | Owns portfolio-level direction, request queue sequencing, maturity framework acceptance, and final decisions for cross-nucleus conflicts. |
| Documentation Coordinator | Maintains global `.instructions` structure, report format, source-of-truth policy, and documentation validation procedure. |
| Nucleus Owner | Owns local nucleus `.instructions`, local implementation constraints, local validation commands, and local blocker accuracy. |
| Safety Reviewer | Reviews changes that affect production/execution boundaries, credentials, treasury, trading, swaps, settlement, payouts, wallet signing, or on-chain writes. |
| Agent Coder | Executes approved documentation/code tasks, preserves boundaries, validates artifacts, and reports results. |

## Review and Approval

| Change Category | Review Required | Approval Required |
|---|---|---|
| Low-risk doc correction | Documentation Coordinator or Agent Coder | No coordinator approval unless semantics change |
| Portfolio status update | Documentation Coordinator | Portfolio Coordinator |
| Maturity classification update | Documentation Coordinator and affected Nucleus Owner | Portfolio Coordinator |
| Sprint/request/task creation | Documentation Coordinator | Portfolio Coordinator |
| Safety boundary change | Safety Reviewer and affected Nucleus Owner | Explicit Portfolio Coordinator approval |
| Execution permission change | Safety Reviewer, affected Nucleus Owner, and Portfolio Coordinator | Explicit Portfolio Coordinator approval |
| Versioning/repository structure change | Documentation Coordinator and affected repo owner | Explicit Portfolio Coordinator approval |

## Update Cadence

- After every completed request/recast/sprint: update status, roadmap, blocker register, and report index if applicable.
- After every maturity change: update maturity register, portfolio status, and affected nucleus status when allowed.
- After every HOLD or blocker change: update blocker register and affected roadmap.
- Before any implementation sprint: confirm the latest global and nucleus `.instructions` do not conflict.

## Coordinator Approval Required

Coordinator approval is required for:

- changing maturity level or portfolio state;
- creating or reordering portfolio request queues;
- modifying global safety boundaries;
- changing execution permission;
- selecting a global docs versioning home;
- repository restructuring;
- moving global docs into a repo;
- adding production-ready or execution-ready claims.

## Nucleus Owner Approval Required

Nucleus owner approval is required when a global change:

- changes local implementation constraints;
- changes local validation expectations;
- changes local safety boundaries;
- changes local roadmap status;
- promotes a local mock/read-only interface toward integration;
- references local runtime behavior as official.

## Safety Rule

Any change that enables or implies production execution, wallet signing, treasury movement, trading, swaps, payouts, settlement, credential use, or on-chain writes requires explicit coordinator approval. It cannot be inferred from documentation updates, maturity labels, request queue placement, or prior local/mock validation.

## Documentation Change Classes

### Low-Risk Doc Correction

Examples:

- typo fix;
- broken internal link correction;
- date/report pointer correction;
- clarifying existing non-execution language.

### Portfolio Status Update

Examples:

- adding completed request status;
- adding validation results;
- recording root non-Git status;
- updating next recommended request.

### Maturity Classification Update

Examples:

- L1 to L2 recovery;
- HOLD to BACKLOG;
- ADVANCE to HOLD;
- updated confidence level.

### Sprint/Request/Task Creation

Examples:

- creating a new REQ document;
- reordering queue priority;
- adding exit criteria.

### Safety Boundary Change

Examples:

- changing a DISABLED flow to GATED;
- adding a new allowed execution path;
- changing credential or wallet handling.

### Execution Permission Change

Examples:

- enabling live trading;
- allowing settlement;
- allowing production DB;
- allowing on-chain writes;
- allowing wallet signing.

### Versioning/Repository Structure Change

Examples:

- making `/opt/Axodus` a Git repo;
- moving global `.instructions` under Core;
- moving global `.instructions` under Documentation;
- creating a dedicated global docs repository.

## L2 Evidence

This policy contributes to L2 recovery by defining who owns, reviews, and approves global docs changes. L2 remains candidate/validated only after validation passes and the versioning decision remains explicitly documented as pending.
